# FTTH Mobily — Critical Domain Quirks

Automation engine is in `Automation/` (facade: `Automation/core.js`). The
toolkit (`FTTH-Mobily-Toolkit/server.js`) drives it. Full guide: `AGENTS.md`.

## Non-negotiable rules (each was a real bug)

- **`networkCategory` is case-sensitive**: default `FTTH Consumer` / `FTTH RCY`.
 Source of truth: `Automation/providers/network-category.js`. Override via UI
 if an env's option list differs.
- **SV notifications are async via B2B**: `UAT-Completed` must wait for the
  B2B `CPE Installation Action (Pending UAT)` first
  (`doWaitForCpeInstallationPendingUat` in `lib/b2b.js`), else the order sticks
  at "UAT Completed".
- **SV payload casing**: `"status": "completed"` (lowercase) and
  `"orderState": "In Progress| UAT Completed"` (space after `|`).
- **Notification delay** lives in `Automation/constants/timing.js`: default 15s,
  Mesh Extender (`WFM-ME-Workflow`) 20s via `notifyDelayForFile()`. Delay is
  applied centrally in `runner/step-executor.js` — do not hardcode per-step.
- **Resume must strip stale per-order IDs** from env (`stripStalePerOrderIds`
  in `runner/resume.js`): `workOrderIdCpe`, `workOrderIdMe`, `serviceOrderId`,
  `odbPatchActionId`, OA IDs. Otherwise notifications fire with a previous
  order's IDs.

## Working rules

- Investigate root cause before editing; verify against the live env (not
  assumptions). Use the `test-telflow` skill for one-shot checks.
- Timing/notification changes must span all providers (`providers/mobily.js`,
  `providers/openaccess.js`, `journeys/builders.js`, `constants/timing.js`)
  unless scoped explicitly.
- `environments/*.bru` contain secrets (password/clientsecret) — never commit.
